Colloidal silver does work against coronavirus, but it has 1 charge per molecule if you would and is a rather dated remedy.
It can kill one cell of the coronavirus per silver molecule.
Nanosilver, which is used by the US military, has 4 charges per molecule, and is far smaller, therefor takes less resources and is less toxic.

Colloidal silver should only be taken if ill, or put in your bong water or something to prevent bacteria and mold.
Nano silver can be taken as a supplement, although it can still be toxic in high enough amounts.

Btw, that bottle of colloidal silver should be $10 if that, and there's probably not real silver in it.

I recently quit working at Papa Johns. One, because an employee I was driving home went batshit for not getting paid leave and punching a dent in my dashboard, and TWO, because their idea of taking precautions involved making a "Pizza Fort" , ringing the doorbell ANYWAY, and then backing up 6 feet as if you're leaving a ransom.

My boss got pissed because I left a box there. I apologized, said I didn't mean to endanger the customer, and she says "No, those boxes cost 50 CENTS, don't do it again."

Yeah fuck them, everyone be safe, I've already got a work from home job now.
